XPathPrecedingMergeIterator Struct

Definition

Iterates over all preceding nodes according to the XPath preceding axis rules, except that nodes are always returned in document order. Merges multiple sets of preceding nodes in document order and removes duplicates.

In this Article

[System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsable(System.ComponentModel.EditorBrowsableState.Never)]
public struct XPathPrecedingMergeIterator
Inheritance
Object
System.ValueType
XPathPrecedingMergeIterator

Properties

Current

Returns the current result navigator.

public System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator Current { get; }
Value
XPathNavigator

The current result navigator.

Remarks

The Current property changes when the MoveNext method sets the Current property to the next node and returns IteratorResult; otherwise, the Current property remains unchanged.

Methods

Create(XmlNavigatorFilter)

Initializes the XPathPrecedingMergeIterator.

public void Create (System.Xml.Xsl.Runtime.XmlNavigatorFilter filter);
filter
XmlNavigatorFilter

An instance of the XmlNavigatorFilter class, which enables you to filter nodes based on the name.

MoveNext(XPathNavigator)

Positions this iterator to the next preceding node in document order.

public System.Xml.Xsl.Runtime.IteratorResult MoveNext (System.Xml.XPath.XPathNavigator input);
input
XPathNavigator

The input node.

Returns
IteratorResult

Returns IteratorResult if there are no more preceding nodes. Returns IteratorResult if the next input node must be fetched first. Returns IteratorResult if the stem.Xml.Xsl.Runtime.XPathPrecedingMergeIterator.Current* property was set to the next node while iterating through the nodes.
